  "text": "Just as for the Martindale ring of quotient it is easily seen that every non-zero (^4,^()-bimodule of Q r (Q \u03b9 > or Q s ) intersect A nontrivially. Hence if A is //-prime or /f-semiprime then so is Q r (Q \u03b9 or Q s ). The following generalizes a result of [CITATION_1] , the proof is essentially the same, using Lemma 10 and the above observation. The same statements can be made about Q \u03b9 or Q\\ we denote Q s = Q. PROPOSITION ",
